    "units": [
        {
            "id": "unit-da-01",
            "title": "Module 1: Excel Basics & Formulas",
            "order": 1,
            "slides": [
                {
                    "id": "da-s01",
                    "order": 1,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Introduction to Excel",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Microsoft Excel Overview</h2><p>Excel is the industry-standard tool for data analysis. Core interface elements:</p><ul><li><strong>Workbook</strong> — the file (.xlsx)</li><li><strong>Worksheet</strong> — individual tabs/sheets</li><li><strong>Cell</strong> — intersection of row &amp; column (e.g. B3)</li><li><strong>Range</strong> — group of cells (e.g. A1:D10)</li></ul><p>Always start with <strong>clean, structured data</strong>: one row per record, headers in row 1, no merged cells.</p>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "da-s02",
                    "order": 2,
                    "type": "interactive",
                    "title": "Key Excel Formulas",
                    "content": {
                        "interaction_type": "tabs",
                        "instructions": "Learn essential Excel formulas by category.",
                        "completion_condition": "all_tabs_visited",
                        "tabs": [
                            {
                                "id": "dat1",
                                "label": "Math",
                                "html": "<h3>Math Functions</h3><ul><li><code>=SUM(A1:A10)</code> — total</li><li><code>=AVERAGE(B1:B10)</code> — mean</li><li><code>=MAX(C1:C10)</code> / <code>=MIN(C1:C10)</code></li><li><code>=ROUND(A1, 2)</code> — round to 2 decimals</li></ul>"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "dat2",
                                "label": "Lookup",
                                "html": "<h3>Lookup Functions</h3><ul><li><code>=VLOOKUP(value, range, col, 0)</code></li><li><code>=XLOOKUP(value, lookup, return)</code> — modern</li><li><code>=INDEX(range, MATCH(val, col, 0))</code></li></ul>"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "dat3",
                                "label": "Logic",
                                "html": "<h3>Logic Functions</h3><ul><li><code>=IF(A1>10, \"High\", \"Low\")</code></li><li><code>=COUNTIF(A1:A10, \"Yes\")</code></li><li><code>=SUMIF(B1:B10, \">100\", C1:C10)</code></li></ul>"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "da-s03",
                    "order": 3,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Data Cleaning",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Data Cleaning in Excel</h2><p>Raw data is rarely perfect. Common issues and fixes:</p><ul><li><strong>Duplicates</strong>: Data → Remove Duplicates</li><li><strong>Blank cells</strong>: Find &amp; Select → Blanks → fill</li><li><strong>Extra spaces</strong>: <code>=TRIM(A1)</code></li><li><strong>Wrong case</strong>: <code>=PROPER(A1)</code>, <code>=UPPER(A1)</code></li><li><strong>Text numbers</strong>: multiply by 1 or use VALUE()</li></ul>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "unit-da-02",
            "title": "Module 2: Charts & Pivot Tables",
            "order": 2,
            "slides": [
                {
                    "id": "da-s04",
                    "order": 1,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Charts & Visualization",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Creating Charts in Excel</h2><p>Choose the right chart for your data:</p><ul><li><strong>Bar / Column</strong> — compare categories</li><li><strong>Line</strong> — show trends over time</li><li><strong>Pie / Donut</strong> — show proportions (max 5-6 slices)</li><li><strong>Scatter</strong> — show correlations</li></ul><p><strong>Steps:</strong> Select data → Insert → Charts → Choose type → Format → Add title &amp; labels.</p>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "da-s05",
                    "order": 2,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Pivot Tables",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Pivot Tables</h2><p>Pivot tables summarize large datasets instantly. Steps:</p><ol><li>Click anywhere in your data range</li><li>Insert → PivotTable → New Sheet</li><li>Drag fields:<ul><li><strong>Rows</strong> — categories (e.g. Region)</li><li><strong>Columns</strong> — sub-categories</li><li><strong>Values</strong> — what to calculate (e.g. SUM of Sales)</li><li><strong>Filters</strong> — slice the view</li></ul></li><li>Right-click → Value Field Settings to change SUM/COUNT/AVERAGE</li></ol>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "da-s06",
                    "order": 3,
                    "type": "quiz",
                    "title": "Excel Final Quiz",
